To determine the internal growth rate, let us first compute the return on assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return on Assets}&=\frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Total Assets}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$2,317,789}{\$22,285,163}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.1040}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The return on assets is 0.1040.**

Now, let us compute the retention ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retention Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,612,789}{\$2,317,789}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.70}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{70\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retention ratio is 70\%.**

To determine the sustainable growth rate, let us first compute the return on equity:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Return on Equity}&=\frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Total Equity}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$2,317,789}{\$13,177,254}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{0.1759}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The return on equity is 0.1759.**

Now, let us compute the retention ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retention Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,612,789}{\$2,317,789}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.70}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{70\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retention ratio is 70\%.**
